            {
                id = "1", speaker = "Scrivener Pol",
                text = "*(He doesn't wait for an answer — terror makes him talk.)* I started two years ago. My sister's debt — the bad kind, the kind with men who *visit.* And I'm a *copyist*, it's the one thing I have, so I started copying the sealed pages by candlelight and selling them, and it *worked*, it paid the men, and I told myself I wasn't *reading* them, just *copying*, just letters, just *shapes.* *(his voice cracks.)* But you can't copy ten thousand words without *some* of them getting *in*, and the things they sealed, Returned — the things Candlekeep decided no one should read — *they're not dangerous spells.* Most of them. They're *true things.* About the Wall. About the Faithless. About what the gods *quietly stopped doing.* *(he stares at his ink-black hands.)* I'm a frightened man copying out the truth for coin, and somewhere in the last two years I *started believing it*, and now I can't stop copying because *someone has to be leaking this*, and I am going to *die* for pages I only meant to *sell.*",
                choices = new[]
