            {
                id = "leak", speaker = "Scrivener Pol",
                text = "*(The fear and the longing war in his face — and the longing, barely, wins.)* All of them. Copied wide. Nailed where the city reads. *(he breathes like a man stepping off a ledge.)* I've *dreamed* it. Lying awake, I've *composed* it — which presses, which nights the watch is thin, which walls the most eyes pass. I know *exactly* how to leak the sealed truth across the whole Gate in a single night, Returned. I've planned my own gallows in *detail*, because the planning was the only way to make the fear hold *still.* *(he grips a sheaf of pages.)* And I never *did* it, because doing it alone is just a quick way to hang. But you — *(hope, naked and dangerous)* — *you* could be the hands that carry, while I'm the hands that *copy.* I make the truth, you *spread* it, and maybe neither of us hangs because neither of us did the whole crime alone. *(fiercely, terrified, alive.)* Yes. *Yes.* Let's leak the lot. Let's make Candlekeep's sealed shame into the thing the whole city reads over breakfast. I've been ready for a year. I just needed someone to be ready *with.*",
